The paper deals with exploration algorithms for autonomous mobile robots, which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in computer science. The use of robots suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The exploration aspect of the paper could also place it in the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. The paper also involves network theory, which could place it in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of algorithms suggests that the paper could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with synchronization and coordination, which could place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Overall, cs.MA and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
